cmatrix
------------------------------------------
CMatrix is based on the screensaver from The Matrix website. It shows text
flying in and out in a terminal like as seen in 'The Matrix' movie. It can
scroll lines all at the same rate or asynchronously and at a user-defined
speed.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-5.2.21-1
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libncursesw10-6.5+20240427-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libncurses-devel-6.5+20240427-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/abishekvashok/cmatrix

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/abishekvashok/cmatrix/archive/refs/tags/v2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cmatrix-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cmatrix-2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cmatrix-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cmatrix-2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cmatrix)
  /usr/bin/cmatrix-tty
  /usr/bin/cmatrix.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cmatrix.README
  /usr/share/doc/cmatrix/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/cmatrix/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/cmatrix/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/cmatrix/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/cmatrix/README
  /usr/share/doc/cmatrix/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/cmatrix.1.gz

